
[1]acrimonious

   ACRIMO'NIOUS, a.

   1. Sharp; bitter; corrosive; abounding with acrimony.

   2. Figuratively, sharpness or severity of temper; bitterness of
   expression proceeding from anger, ill-nature, or petulance.
